
    THE teachers were shocked when they arrived at school on Monday morning to find all the computers stolen.  Principal Paul Mokhosi of Clocolan High School, near Ficksburg said thugs stole all the school computers and laptops. “They gained entry through the roof and disarmed the alarm.  if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=1643732282&t=artid%3d7862e2f3-e168-4890-a4e4-6b8a11acb9a5%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=1643732282&t=artid%3d7862e2f3-e168-4890-a4e4-6b8a11acb9a5%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>“They then   broke the door to get to where the  computer lab keys were kept,” said Mokhosi. “I think the thieves got the information from someone who knows the school very well. “This is definitely an inside job.” He said the thugs even took a cellphone that had been confiscated from a pupil. “These cruel thugs took almost everything.  I’m sure they had to use a vehicle to collect the goods,” Mokhosi told Daily Sun. Police spokesman Captain Phumelelo Dhlamini said: “A case of business robbery has been opened at Clocolan Police Station. “Police are investigating a case of theft after computers and laptops were stolen from Cocolan High School.  “Anyone with information should visit Clocolan cops or call 08600 1011.” 
